dcterms:description: The HIV dataset contains 35 patients (positive) and 35 seronegative controls (negative). Each modality graph is with 90 nodes and edge weights are calculated as correlations between brain regions. The dataset is constructed following the methods described in the reference.
dcterms:title: Human Immunodeficiency Virus Infection (HIV)

dcterms:description: The Bipolar Disorder dataset consists of 52 bipolar subjects in euthymia and 45 healthy controls with matched age and gender. It stimulates 82 brain regions, according to Freesurfer-generated cortical/subcortical gray matter regions.
dcterms:title: Bipolar Disorder (BP)
